brief_summary.textblock:
In Japan, post-approval execution of post marketing surveillance (PMS) is requested by the
      Japanese Pharmaceutical Affairs Law (J-PAL) in order to accumulate safety and efficacy data
      for reexamination. Reexamination period is defined by Japanese Pharmaceutical Affairs Low
      (J-PAL). New ingredient is 8 years for reexamination. Eight years after approval of a new
      substance, results of PMS need to be submitted as a part of reexamination dossier to the
      Japanese regulatory authority, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare (MHLW).

clinical_study.brief_title: PMS of Trazenta on the Long-term Use as Add-on Therapy

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion criteria:

        Patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus who are treated with anti-diabetic drugs and have
        never been treated with Trazenta® Tablets (linagliptin) before enrollment will be
        included.

        Exclusion criteria:

        None

intervention.description: 1 tablet of 5 mg Trazenta tablets once daily

clinical_study.official_title: Post Marketing Surveillance on Long Term Drug Use of Trazenta® Tablets as add-on Therapy in Patients With Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus

oversight_info.authority: Japan: Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare

primary_outcome.measure: The primary endpoint to assess safety of Trazenta Tablets is the number (%) of patients with drug related adverse events

required_header.download_date: ClinicalTrials.gov processed this data on June 04, 2014
required_header.link_text: Link to the current ClinicalTrials.gov record.

secondary_outcome.measure: The change between baseline and observation period in Haemoglobin A1c (HbA1c)

clinical_study.study_design: Observational Model: Cohort, Time Perspective: Prospective
